  "prompt": "When is it likely that the proposed extended maternity leave from 12 to 26 weeks will be implemented for private sectors in India?",
  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, the proposal to extend maternity leave in India from 12 to 26 weeks for the private sector had not been officially implemented. The Maternity Benefit (Amendment) Act, which came into effect in April 2017, increased maternity leave from 12 weeks to 26 weeks for women working in organizations with 10 or more employees.\n\nFor updates beyond October 2023, it would be best to consult recent government announcements, news articles, or official publications to find out the current status of this proposal and any timelines for its implementation in the private sector.",
